  "body": "I am using the hardhat vyper plugin to compile the CurveFi contract and it compiles successfully with running docker.\r\n\r\nWhen using CircleCI with a Node image and enabled \"Remote docker\", the vyper compiler **cannot run** because it uses mounting to put the vyper contracts in the container with this command: \r\n\r\n`docker run -v $(pwd):/code vyperlang/vyper:0.1.0b17 -f combined_json /code/contracts/curve/CurveFi.vy\r\n`\r\n\r\nIn CircleCI, mounting on a docker container is disabled and the workaround is the following:\r\n```\r\n    docker create -v /code --name code vyperlang/vyper:0.1.0b17 /bin/true\r\n    docker cp $(pwd)/contracts/curve/CurveFi.vy code:/code\r\n    docker run --volumes-from code vyperlang/vyper:0.1.0b17 -f combined_json /code/CurveFi.vy\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor example, a flag can be put whether to avoid mounting or use the original way, or the command can be replaced by the above three commands. This way, all CircleCI Hardhat builds using Node images will be able to use the vyper compiler.\r\n\r\nReferences:\r\nhttps://circleci.com/docs/2.0/building-docker-images/#mounting-folders\r\n",
